criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age: 20 - 80 years;

          -  Gastroesophageal reflux disease as evidence by gastroscopy and pH-monitoring;

          -  HH type I, II

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Age < 20 years and > 80 years;

          -  Unable to undergo laparoscopic fundoplication due to: severe comorbidities (ASA III
             and more), previous major surgery with severe adhesions, etc.;

          -  HH type III, IV;

          -  BMI < 16 and > 45 kg/m²;

          -  Pregnancy (in females);

          -  Oesophageal motility disorders;

          -  Oesophageal peptic strictures;

          -  Oesophageal diverticula, other types (i.e. non-reflux) of chronic esophagitis,
             connective tissue disorders (e.g. scleroderma);

          -  History of oesophageal/gastric/duodenal surgery including vagotomy;

          -  Relapsing course of ulcer disease/hyperacid gastritis including complicated by delayed
             gastric/duodenal emptying
